{"title_page": "Mur Pano language", "text_new": "{{short description|Austronesian language spoken in Papua New Guinea}}\n{{distinguish|Panoan languages}}\n{{Infobox language\n  |name=Mur Pano\n  |nativename=Pano\n  |states=[[Papua New Guinea]]\n  |region=[[Madang Province]]\n  |speakers=700\u2013800<!--E18 conflated L1 and L2-->\n  |date = 2012\n  |ref = <ref name=proposed>[http://www-01.sil.org/iso639-3/cr_files/2013-004_tkv.pdf]</ref>\n  |speakers2=1,000 total (2012). \n  |familycolor=Austronesian\n  |fam2=[[Malayo-Polynesian languages|Malayo-Polynesian]]\n  |fam3=[[Oceanic languages|Oceanic]]\n  |fam4=[[Western Oceanic languages|Western Oceanic]]\n  |fam5=[[Ngero\u2013Vitiaz languages|Ngero\u2013Vitiaz]]\n  |fam6=[[Korap languages|Korap]]\n  |iso3=tkv\n  |glotto=murp1234\n  |glottorefname=Mur Pano\n}}\n\n'''Mur Pano''', or simply '''Pano''', is an [[Austronesian language]] spoken by about three quarters of the thousand inhabitants of Mur village on the north coast of [[Madang Province]], [[Papua New Guinea]].   The other quarter of the population speaks [[Molet language|Molet]] as their primary language.\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n{{North New Guinea languages}}\n{{Languages of Papua New Guinea}}\n\n[[Category:Languages of Madang Province]]\n[[Category:Korap languages]]\n[[Category:Articles citing ISO change requests]]\n\n\n{{NNGuinea-lang-stub}}\n", "text_old": "{{short description|Austronesian language spoken in Papua New Guinea}}\n{{distinguish|Panoan languages}}\n{{Infobox language\n  |name=Mur Pano\n  |nativename=Pano\n  |region=[[Madang Province]], [[Papua New Guinea]]\n  |speakers=700\u2013800<!--E18 conflated L1 and L2-->\n  |date = 2012\n  |ref = <ref name=proposed>[http://www-01.sil.org/iso639-3/cr_files/2013-004_tkv.pdf]</ref>\n  |speakers2=1,000 total (2012). \n  |familycolor=Austronesian\n  |fam2=[[Malayo-Polynesian languages|Malayo-Polynesian]]\n  |fam3=[[Oceanic languages|Oceanic]]\n  |fam4=[[Western Oceanic languages|Western Oceanic]]\n  |fam5=[[Ngero\u2013Vitiaz languages|Ngero\u2013Vitiaz]]\n  |fam6=[[Korap languages|Korap]]\n  |iso3=tkv\n  |glotto=murp1234\n  |glottorefname=Mur Pano\n}}\n\n'''Mur Pano''', or simply '''Pano''', is an [[Austronesian language]] spoken by about three quarters of the thousand inhabitants of Mur village on the north coast of [[Madang Province]], [[Papua New Guinea]].   The other quarter of the population speaks [[Molet language|Molet]] as their primary language.\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n{{North New Guinea languages}}\n{{Languages of Papua New Guinea}}\n\n[[Category:Languages of Madang Province]]\n[[Category:Korap languages]]\n[[Category:Articles citing ISO change requests]]\n\n\n{{NNGuinea-lang-stub}}\n", "name_user": "Austronesier", "label": "safe", "comment": "", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Mur_Pano_language"}
